content:
@Eoganacht | BULK I regret to say that I do not agree with even a single sentence you wrote in the Foundation. In the parallel universe you inhabit, alt accounts might be common in RTS games, but in this universe, they are actively fought against.

Take Travian, for example a game with over 1.5 million players and incredibly strict anti-multi-account policies. The same applies to Gameforge titles, which boast over 400 million registered players worldwide. We played Ogame, one of their flagship titles, for years back in the 2000s, and it maintained a zero-tolerance policy toward multi-accounting. Beyond that, even 'account sitting' is banned in most of these games; it is only permitted under strict moderator supervision with special authorization. It is truly ridiculous that we are here today debating whether multi-accounting is legitimate.

It seems it will take you some time to realize that your 'parallel reality' does not apply here. However, the cost of this oversight will very likely be a stagnant player base. If there is one universal human trait, it is a shared dislike for rowing in vain. A game environment that supports multi-accounting creates exactly that feeling. Over time, players lose interest as they feel their efforts are futile. Please, when discussing these matters, try to think 5, 10, or even 50 steps ahead.
